rsnapshot 0.9.0

rsnapshot is a filesystem snapshot utility. It can take incremental
snapshots of local and remote filesystems for any number of machines.

rsnapshot comes with ABSOLUTELY NO WARRANTY.  This is free software,
and you are welcome to redistribute it under certain conditions.
See the GNU General Public Licence for details.

INSTALLATION
	
	QUICK INSTALLATION
		su root
		make install

	THE HARD WAY
		su root
		cp rsnapshot /usr/local/bin/rsnapshot
		chown 0:0 /usr/local/bin/rsnapshot
		chmod 755 /usr/local/bin/rsnapshot
		
		mkdir -p /usr/local/man/man1/
		cp rsnapshot.1 /usr/local/man/man1/
		chown 0:0 /usr/local/man/man1/rsnapshot.1
		chmod 644 /usr/local/man/man1/rsnapshot.1
		
		cp rsnapshot.conf /etc/rsnapshot.conf
		chown 0:0 /etc/rsnapshot.conf
		chmod 600 /etc/rsnapshot.conf
		
QUICK START (for the impatient)
	see the README file if you want the 30 second version
		
CONFIGURATION
	edit /etc/rsnapshot.conf to suit your tastes
	"man rsnapshot" for the full documentation
